Ratings.comment: The most amazing class I've ever taken. Riley was truly incredible and connected deeply with each of his students. Our class was so close and we had amazing class discussions everyday. Never once did I dread going to Riley's class.His assignments were enjoyable to complete and allowed us to have enough time to complete. Definitely recommend taking

A true king. He is so caring towards his students and is accessible outside of class. For the first half of the semester we had a weekly paper that was due and they were pretty lengthy; towards the end he changed a lot of them into discussion posts instead. The grading criteria was very clear and wasn't hard to do well on the assignments.

This man is an angel. Cares so much about the content and the well-being of the students. He is a therapist outside of this class and his empathy and concern for others really show. Classes also are discussion-based with no tests only weekly papers that don't take long. 10/10 recommend

This man is my favorite person in the world easily.  I cannot stress it enough how much I loved this class and professor Whiting.  He is hilarious and kind and makes every class incredible.  He is the most compassionate, understanding person ever. He really really cares for his students and it meant so much having him as a teacher.  He is the BEST!

Professor Whiting is the best professor I've ever had by far. He genuinely cares about your personal well-being and is honest about himself, building a great relationship with students. Lectures are interactive (and fun!) and class ends up being enjoyable. I put attendance as mandatory, but his attendance policy is lenient and he wants you to pass.

I cannot say enough good things about Riley! He is so knowledgeable about the material, and intentionally structures the class so we each get out of it what we want to learn. Every class is engaging and we are consistently pushed to relate the class to our own lives. This class was consistently a joy and Riley is a wonderful instructor!

Riley has been one of my favorite professors at OSU. He genuinely cares about his students and always makes lectures super enjoyable. The class itself is pretty easy. Each week there is a paper and questions that go with a reading that you have unlimited tries on. If you are looking for an enjoyable GE and amazing professor take this class!

He is AMAZING. He is super kind and is very passionate. He has inspired me in so many ways throughout this entire course. There is a weekly paper but it is 2 pages and short. There are no tests and the midterm/final were also papers. This is the most enjoyable class I have ever taken. He was able to create an open kind atmosphere to debate in class

He's literally been my favorite professor at OSU so far. genuinely cares so much about his students and wants them to understand the content that he also is very knowledgeable in and cares about. the way he teaches makes it easy to learn the content that's also very interesting and useful for life. 100% recommend Riley!!!

Professor Whiting is truly a good guy. He opens up to you when he doesnt have to, he gives you just enough homework, considerate of you having other work. He just to take his jobs serious, yet makes it extremely fun. He deserves a raise.

Hes the best professor that Ive had ever. Hes a great teacher and makes coming to class very exciting. He is very caring and will do anything for you if you need it. I definitely recommend taking any class that he teaches because it will be a great experience no what. Genuinely the greatest teacher there is and Im glad I got to take his class!!
By no means a class to avoid; if you can or have to, take this class.

He is by far the best professor I have ever had. He is understanding and supportive. Criteria is clear and content is actually made interesting. Doesn't just stand up there and lecture, he actually engages the class. 10/10 would take again.
The best professor. One essay a week, group discussions in class, and quizzes with unlimited tries. Super enjoyable class and teaches great lessons.

Riley is truly an amazing person. He genuinely cares so much about all of his students. He is funny and very understanding. Class is easy, the topics are relatable and apply to everyday life. Does an amazing job of explaining everything. Would highly recommend! :)

Riley is a great professor that is very caring and will go out of his way to make sure that you are genuinely okay in life. He is a very funny and he makes class very enjoyable and easy to understand. The content itself is very interesting and he makes it even better. Highly recommend this class!

This class is very easy to get an A in. Each week consists of an essay, a quiz (unlimited tries), a discussion post, and discussion responses. It may seem like a lot at first but it is very manageable and has interesting topics. The class is asynchronous but the prof still was extremely caring during Covid and was very accessible outside of class.

The class content was great, but Karis was horrible. She never answered emails, took months to grade assignments, and pawned almost all of her grading onto the TA. She cancelled class often for no reason, and two of those times were a class before an exam. I recommend the course, but not with this instructor.

Amazing professor & super interesting class! I took it online during summer semester, and my week consisted of a few readings, quiz based off of readings, and discussion post. She offers tons of extra credit. Turn in your work, and you'll be good!

I would give her a 6/5 if I could, Professor Inboden is a very friendly and helpful professor. She gave LOTS of extra credit and fairly returned commonly missed points on quizzes. The paper she even allows you to submit early for feedback before you submit for the due date! The course itself is also super interesting so I'd definitely recommend!!

She is super caring and gives us lots of extra credits. If the majority got quiz questions wrong, she gave us return points. Her paper isn't hard, just put the effort in, and you will get a good grade. Also, you can learn a lot in HDFS 2410. Plz take her class.

He was a really cool professor, his lectures were very interesting and he seemed very engaged in helping students understand the topics. He does require group discussions every week in class so attendance is mandatory but allows makeups if you miss class.

Dr. Mallory was okay. The class was pretty easy. This was his first time teaching this course, so it could have been a little better with the way it was structured. There were weekly discussions, and your group had to submit a document recording a synopsis of what you talked about. I am not even sure if he would read these, but we always got 100%.

SEI.Subject: HDFS
SEI.Class Name: Human Sexuality and Intersectionality Across the Lifespan

Ratings.comment:
Probably the sweetest professor at OSU, but just as strict as she is kind. Which kinda feels ingenuous. She perfectly fits the stereotype that the nicest professors are often the toughest when it comes to leniency and vice versa.

Easy enough class tho, just don't expect her to cut you any slack if you need it, unlike most professors.

I can't speak much on prof Wong because the class was online asynchronous so I didn't really interact with her. The class was easy though, I learned a great deal from it and found the content interesting.

Dr. Wong is wonderful. After taking Lifespan Development with her in the spring, I can say I thoroughly enjoy her knowledge and lecturing style. For her young age, she is full of knowledge that more HDFS majors can utilize in their careers. I could not recommend Dr. Wong more.

Professor Wong is great, she was one of the kindest professors I've had. Lectures are long but she makes them interesting, just make sure to get everything off the slides when she goes through them because she doesn't post them. Lots of opportunities for extra credit, 3 exams that you can have a cheat sheet for. Easy and interesting content.

She's absolutely the best! This is my first semester at OSU and I was a little nervous about the professors but her classes are amazing. You can tell she loves teaching and engaging with her students. She's really passionate and she actually wants you to learn. I'd definitely take another course with her.

This was such an easy class but very interesting. There are 3 exams that you can have a note sheet for. You have to come to class to do the FMPs which are random. Lots of extra credit opportunities. Dr. Wong loves teaching and the subject she is teaching.

Such an amazing professor who is very clearly passionate about the material. As long as you attend lecture and take decent notes, this class will be a breeze. There's also plenty of opportunities for extra credit to boost your grade.

the sweetest lady and super easy but interesting class. just take good notes and the exams will be fine- you get a page of notes to use on exams. doesnt take attendance but if you miss class you miss the notes. probably the kindest professor ive ever had, so passionate about the material.

I absolutely loved having her as a professor, I would highly recommend! She is truly passionate about the topics covered in this course and made learning fun! She gave many opportunities to meet with her outside of class and will gladly help you understand concepts better, genuinely the best class Ive ever taken. No homework besides easy surveys
BEST TEACHER EVER. take this class !!! She is kind, cooperative, and WANTS to help you. Class is very interesting too. Must take.

Professor Wong was amazing! This was probably the easiest college class I've taken. There were only weekly quizzes, a few paragraph papers, and a few surveys but no exams and extra credit on the last assignments. I loved her feedback from our papers and she was always so polite in emails! She really cares about her students and made class great!
Professor Wong is amazing. She makes class entertaining and fun and makes exams clear and understandable. She really cares about her students and their success.
Jen Wong is the female Jesus.

Professor Wong genuinely cares about how her students are doing. No homework in the class. Attendance was mandatory for 4 papers that were randomly assigned in class (if you show up for them and write at least a paragraph you get 4/4). Midterms and finals were easy and you can use a sheet of notes.

Great class! You need to show up because there are random 5 minute papers, but the class is a joy to be in. Jen's passion and enthusiasm for human development is obvious from the second you walk into her class. She always has a huge smile on her face and is just a wonderful person to learn from and work with

I LOVED her class. Her lectures are really interesting. You have to do 5 papers for participation in class, really short and opinion based, but if you do more, you get extra credit (so attend class). No online notes, so its imp to be in class, which really helps on exams- which are basically open note (cheat sheet allowed).

Professor Wong (Jen) gives really engaging lectures. In class, I was never bored because she encourages very casual participation and lots of discussion which is interesting because my class was very diverse. We never knew what stories we were about to hear and I laughed during every lecture.

I LOVE JEN WONG! She is the best professor I've had so far at OSU. Super easy A as long as you come to lecture. Attendance isn't mandatory but she gives 6 "5-minute papers" at random times throughout the semester. If you go to lecture you definitely don't need the book. Plus you get a full page of notes on every exam!! I highly recommend this class

Jen Wong was a great professor. She is extremely helpful and tries her best to make class entertaining.  The book isn't needed for her HDFS 2400 class, I never opened it up and still received an A in the class

Jen Wong is the most amazing professor!! I took her HDFS 2400 class and I am now a research assistant in her lab. It has been so great getting to work with herbecause she truly cares so much about her students. If you ever get the opportunity to work with Jen or learn from her don't pass it up because it has been one of my best experiences at OSU.

I am a research assistant in Dr. Jen Wong's lab, and it was been a very enjoyable and educational experience. She works hard to make sure that myself and the other assistants know what we are doing and how the research process works, and genuinely cares about our well-being outside of the lab. I definitely recommend taking a class with her!

I have been a research assistant for a few semesters, and I plan on continuing next semester. I also had Jen as my HDFS 2400 professor and I would highly recommend that class. Jen goes out of her way for her students and research assistants. She makes meetings/lectures fun and enjoyable as well. I have learned a lot Jen and the experience is great!

I have been a research assistant for a few semesters now. She has helped develop my skills as a researcher and has provided me with structural feedback to become a more critical thinker. I highly recommend working with Dr. Wong.

I work in Jen's research lab and I find it a great research enviornment to be in!  She is always helpful and very personable with all the students!  She is great to work with and I will be continuing research with her next semester!  I have learned alot and gained great experience.
